HEADWORD: Seminist
<hw>Sem"i*nist</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <fld>(Biol.)</fld>
<def>A believer in the old theory that the newly created being is formed
by the admixture of the seed of the male with the supposed seed of the
female.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Seminoles</ent>⟦br⟧
